'''''Air Raiders''''' is an [[action game]] developed by [[M Network|M-Network]] and published by [[Mattel]]. The game was released for the [[Atari 2600]] in 1982. The game received mixed reviews from critics.

==Gameplay==
[[File:Air_Raiders_Screenshot.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The player destroying an enemy aircraft]]
Air Raiders is a [[flight simulator]] whose the player has the view of an airstrip as seen from the cockpit of a jet fighter. The goal of the game was to shoot as many enemies as possible, while avoiding the enemy's cannon fire and landing safely before the fuel runs out.

